Program: Outlook
Title: 01/08/2011
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00j3p6v
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 2 Aug 2011
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, the story of Marina Nemat who was arrested in 1982 when she was only 16 and taken to Iran's notorious Evin prison. There she was tortured, threatened with execution and forced to marry her interrogator. She was eventually released in 1984, but it was more than 20 years before she could talk to anyone about what she had gone through. She tells Jo Fidgen her remarkable story. Show less